---
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-24" data-reveal>
  <div class="grid items-center gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div>
      <p class="text-accent-hi text-sm font-semibold">AI-assisted docs</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 max-w-xl text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-balance sm:text-4xl">
        Docs that keep themselves up to date
      </h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-4 max-w-xl">
        Your knowledge base lives next to your issues — not in a separate Confluence. When an
        issue closes, NextTrack proposes an update to the right article, in place. A human
        approves it by moving the doc-update issue to Done — the tracker itself is the review
        surface.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-line bg-panel rounded-xl border p-5">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-fg-muted font-mono text-xs">NT-158</span>
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Update deploy runbook</span>
        </div>
        <span class="border-accent/40 bg-accent/15 text-accent-hi rounded-full border px-2 py-0.5 text-[11px] font-medium">
          AI proposal
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="border-line bg-panel-hi mt-4 rounded-lg border p-3.5 font-mono text-xs leading-6">
        <p class="text-fg-muted">## Deploying to production</p>
        <p class="text-fg-muted">1. Build the Docker images</p>
        <p class="text-fg-muted">2. Run database migrations</p>
        <p class="rounded bg-[var(--color-status-done)]/10 px-1 text-[var(--color-status-done)]">
          + 3. Reindex Elasticsearch before opening traffic
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-line text-fg-muted mt-4 flex items-center justify-between border-t pt-3 text-xs">
        <span>Approve → move to Done</span>
        <span>Discard → Cancel</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
